rom tree (<ph id=\"ph1\">@UnitName</ph>)","pos":[20385,20416],"source":"Unit name from tree (@UnitName)"},{"content":"If you restrict a column to a specific unit of the reporting tree, print the unit name in the column header.","pos":[20427,20535]},{"content":"Unit description (<ph id=\"ph1\">@UnitDesc</ph>)","pos":[20720,20748],"source":"Unit description (@UnitDesc)"},{"content":"If you restrict a column to a specific unit of the reporting tree, print the unit description in the column header.","pos":[20762,20877]},{"content":"Book Code (<ph id=\"ph1\">@BookCode</ph>)","pos":[21055,21076],"source":"Book Code (@BookCode)"},{"content":"Print the book code that is specified in the column.","pos":[21097,21149]},{"content":"Blank line (<ph id=\"ph1\">@Blank</ph>)","pos":[21390,21409],"source":"Blank line (@Blank)"},{"content":"Insert an empty line in the column header.","pos":[21432,21474]},{"pos":[21728,21764],"content":"Create a conditional spanning header","linkify":"Create a conditional spanning header","nodes":[{"content":"Create a conditional spanning header","pos":[0,36]}]},{"content":"Conditional spanning headers can span multiple columns that are based on specific period data.","pos":[21766,21860]},{"content":"For example, if you have a budget report for the fiscal year and want to display the actual budgets of past months together with the projected budgets of future months, you can use a conditional spanning header to automatically update the report header.","pos":[21861,22114]},{"content":"Be aware of the following situations when you create a conditional spanning header:","pos":[22115,22198]},{"content":"Any stop condition (<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Spread to<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> field) that is matched before a start condition (<bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Spread From<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept> field) is ignored.","pos":[22204,22321],"source":"Any stop condition (**Spread to** field) that is matched before a start condition (**Spread From** field) is ignored."},{"content":"For example, column B has the spread condition defined as BASE+1 to BASE, BASE is in column C, and BASE+1 is in column D. In this case, the stop condition in column C is ignored, and the printing of the header starts at column D.","pos":[22322,22551]},{"content":"If you specify column headers that overlap, they overlap when they are printed on the report.","pos":[22556,22649]},{"content":"The report is generated, but the following warning appears in the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Report Queue Status<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> field: “Column headers using Base intersect with other column headers and may cause overlapping text.”","pos":[22650,22842],"source":" The report is generated, but the following warning appears in the **Report Queue Status** field: “Column headers using Base intersect with other column headers and may cause overlapping text.”"},{"content":"For example, the header definition on column B is B to BASE+1, and the header definition on column D is BASE+1 to F. In this case, the headers are printed on top of each other and are unreadable.","pos":[22843,23038]},{"content":"Whenever BASE is used in a <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Spread from/Spread to<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> definition, be sure to view the report that is generated, to see whether the headers overlap.","pos":[23039,23185],"source":" Whenever BASE is used in a **Spread from/Spread to** definition, be sure to view the report that is generated, to see whether the headers overlap."},{"content":"If you specify BASE in the spread definition in a No Print (<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>NP<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>) column, it's ignored, regardless of what is defined in the column definition.","pos":[23190,23335],"source":"If you specify BASE in the spread definition in a No Print (**NP**) column, it's ignored, regardless of what is defined in the column definition."},{"content":"Essentially, this scenario is the same as not creating a column header definition.","pos":[23336,23418]},{"content":"For conditional printing columns (<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>P<ph id=\"ph1\">&amp;lt;</ph>B<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>, <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>P<ph id=\"ph2\">&amp;gt;</ph>=B<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept>), conditional spanning headers behave like any regular column header definition.","pos":[23423,23561],"source":"For conditional printing columns (**P&lt;B**, **P&gt;=B**), conditional spanning headers behave like any regular column header definition."},{"content":"For example, if the condition is false, any subsequent column matching for the spread condition starts the printing of the header.","pos":[23562,23692]},{"pos":[23699,23735],"content":"Create a conditional spanning header","linkify":"Create a conditional spanning header","nodes":[{"content":"Create a conditional spanning header","pos":[0,36]}]},{"content":"In Report Designer, open the column definition to modify.","pos":[23741,23798]},{"content":"Double-click a header cell.","pos":[23803,23830]},{"content":"In the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Column Header<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> dialog box, enter the column header text.","pos":[23835,23901],"source":"In the **Column Header** dialog box, enter the column header text."},{"content":"Alternatively, click <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Insert AutoText<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>, and select an option.","pos":[23902,23965],"source":" Alternatively, click **Insert AutoText**, and select an option."},{"pos":[23971,24045],"content":"In the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Format options<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> field, select a formatting style for the header.","source":"In the **Format options** field, select a formatting style for the header."},{"content":"Specify a period relative to the base period that is specified when the report is generated.","pos":[24050,24142]},{"content":"In the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Spread from<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> and <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Spread to<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept> fields, enter one of the following values: <bpt id=\"p3\">**</bpt>BASE<ept id=\"p3\">**</ept>, <bpt id=\"p4\">**</bpt>BASE-X<e