ions.","pos":[65604,65798],"source":"**Note:** When you use a base row calculation in a column definition, make sure that each row definition that is used with this column definition contains at least one base row for calculations."},{"pos":[65805,65859],"content":"Divide the amount in a column by the number of periods","linkify":"Divide the amount in a column by the number of periods","nodes":[{"content":"Divide the amount in a column by the number of periods","pos":[0,54]}]},{"content":"You can divide the amount in a column by a specified number of periods.","pos":[65861,65932]},{"content":"For example, the formula <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>B/Periods<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> divides the value in column B by the number of periods in column B. If the calculation spans multiple columns, specify the number of periods to use in the calculation.","pos":[65933,66139],"source":" For example, the formula **B/Periods** divides the value in column B by the number of periods in column B. If the calculation spans multiple columns, specify the number of periods to use in the calculation."},{"content":"For example, the formula <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>(B+C)/Periods<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> adds the amounts in column B and column C, and then divides the result by the period value.","pos":[66140,66274],"source":" For example, the formula **(B+C)/Periods** adds the amounts in column B and column C, and then divides the result by the period value."},{"pos":[66276,66284],"content":"See also","linkify":"See also","nodes":[{"content":"See also","pos":[0,8]}]},{"pos":[66295,66375],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Row definitions in financial reporting<ept id=\"p1\">](row-definitions-financial-reporting.md)</ept>","source":"[Row definitions in financial reporting](row-definitions-financial-reporting.md)"},{"pos":[66377,66481],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Advanced formatting options in financial reporting<ept id=\"p1\">](advanced-formatting-options-financial-reporting.md)</ept>","source":"[Adv